<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-02-23T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-02-23T18:00:00-05:00" n="121" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d121">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">813.00/1057: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Salvador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Jay</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">San
                                        Salvador</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-02-23T17:00:00-06:00"><hi rend="italic">February 23,
                                        1921—5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received February 24—12:53
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>9. Pact of the Union of the four Central American States was ratified
                            today by the National Congress.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Jay</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
